DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in creating a more vibrant and walkable Tor
 onto for everyone? Share your ideas\, socialize\, and enjoy a meal with us
  at Toronto's first community-organized Pedestrian Summit!\n\nAs cities li
 ke Montreal\, Paris\, and New York make big investments in pedestrian prio
 rity projects\, is Toronto lagging behind the global stage? Help us organi
 ze and shape an agenda for making the city a better and safer city for ped
 estrians of all ages.\n\nThe summit is open to all walkable city enthusias
 ts\, residents\, community advocates\, city builders\, and organizational 
 representatives interested in making Toronto a pedestrian-friendly city.\n
 \nTickets include a light meal and refreshments.\n\nAfter the event there 
 will be an informal social at Trinity Common (a 10 minute walk from the ve
 nue).\n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n
  \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\
 n \n\nSponsored by:\n\n \n\nThe Biking Lawyer\n\n \n\nPresented by:\n\n \n
 \n8 80 Cities\, Cycle Toronto\, Friends and Families for Safe Streets\, Gr
 een Neighbours Network\, Jane's Walk\, Strong Towns Toronto\, Toronto Clim
 ate Action Network\, Toronto Environmental Alliance\, TTCriders\, Walk Tor
 onto\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/pedestrian_summit_2026
LOCATION:Cecil Community Center\n58 Cecil St\nToronto ON M5T 1N6\nCA
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/pedestrian_summit_2026
